Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 10:25:11 +0200
From: Patrick Goubau <goubau@mblg.ucl.ac.be>

A third case of BSE has been described in Belgium. It is difficult to
continue to describe these Belgian cases as 'sporadic' or 'isolated'. The
case occurred in a herd in Waarschoot in the same part of the country as the
previous case. The 124 other cows of the herd have been destroyed and their
brains are being investigated.
--
