Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 17:59:03 -0500
From: Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
Source: FSNET and Reuters
BELGIUM FINDS THIRD MAD COW CASE, DESTROYS HERD

BRUSSELS -- Belgium's farm authorities were cited as saying today that a
third case of mad cow disease had been discovered in the northwest of the
country, leading to the destruction of a 124-strong herd of cattle.
Government veterinarians examined a five-year-old cow on March 9, confirming
BSE (bovine spongiform encephalopathy) earlier today. The European
Commission and other European Union members had been informed, the farm
ministry said in a statement.
